---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import AffiliateLink from '../components/AffiliateLink.astro';

const meta = {
  title: 'AI Website Hosting Guide: Where to Host AI-Built Sites (2025)',
  description: 'Where to host websites built with AI tools like v0.dev, Durable, Framer. Free hosting options, Vercel vs Netlify vs traditional hosting explained.',
  image: '/og-image.svg',
  keywords: ['AI website hosting', 'Vercel vs Netlify', 'where to host AI website', 'host v0.dev site', 'Durable hosting'],
};
---

<Layout {...meta}>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-[#FEF9F3] py-12 sm:py-16 md:py-20">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
      <p class="text-[10px] sm:text-xs font-black text-[#E07A5F] mb-4 tracking-[0.3em] uppercase">
        Complete Guide · Updated 2025
      </p>

      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-black mb-6 leading-tight">
        AI Website Hosting Guide
      </h1>

      <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl md:text-2xl text-gray-700 mb-8">
        You built a website with AI. Now where do you put it? Hosting options depend on which AI builder you used. Some include hosting, some don't. Here's what you need to know.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-[#E07A5F]/10 border-2 border-[#E07A5F] rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
          Quick answer: <AffiliateLink href="https://v0.dev">v0.dev</AffiliateLink> sites → Host on <AffiliateLink href="https://vercel.com">Vercel</AffiliateLink> (free). Durable/Framer → Hosting included (paid). If you exported code, <AffiliateLink href="https://vercel.com">Vercel</AffiliateLink> or Netlify are best free options.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- By Builder -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Hosting by AI Builder
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <!-- v0.dev -->
      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4"><AffiliateLink href="https://v0.dev">v0.dev</AffiliateLink> → <AffiliateLink href="https://vercel.com">Vercel</AffiliateLink></h3>
        
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">v0.dev is built by Vercel. They want you to host there. Best integration, one-click deployment.</p>

        <p class="font-bold mb-2">Free tier includes:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-4">
          <li>• Unlimited projects</li>
          <li>• Automatic deployments from Git</li>
          <li>• SSL certificates (HTTPS)</li>
          <li>• Edge network (fast global delivery)</li>
          <li>• Serverless functions</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="font-bold mb-2">Free tier limits:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• Vercel-branded domain (yourname.vercel.app)</li>
          <li>• 100 GB bandwidth per month</li>
          <li>• Build logs limited (24 hours)</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="font-bold mb-2">Pro tier ($20/month) adds:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• Custom domain (yourname.com)</li>
          <li>• Unlimited bandwidth</li>
          <li>• Priority support</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="text-gray-700 mt-4"><strong>Recommendation:</strong> Start with Vercel free tier. Upgrade to Pro only if you hit bandwidth limits or need custom domain urgently.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Durable -->
      <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4"><AffiliateLink href="https://durable.co">Durable</AffiliateLink> → Included (Locked In)</h3>
        
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Durable hosting is included in subscription. You can't export your site, so you can't host elsewhere. You're paying for hosting + platform + support bundled together.</p>

        <p class="font-bold mb-2">What's included:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-4">
          <li>• Hosting (Durable's servers)</li>
          <li>• SSL certificate</li>
          <li>• Durable subdomain or custom domain</li>
          <li>• Platform updates and maintenance</li>
          <li>• Customer support</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="text-gray-700 mt-4"><strong>The catch:</strong> Stop paying = site goes offline immediately. No export option. You're locked into Durable hosting forever.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Framer -->
      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4"><AffiliateLink href="https://framer.com">Framer</AffiliateLink> → Included (Mostly Locked In)</h3>
        
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Framer hosting is included. You CAN export code, but it's messy. Most users stay on Framer hosting for convenience.</p>

        <p class="font-bold mb-2">What's included:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-4">
          <li>• Fast global hosting (CDN)</li>
          <li>• SSL certificates</li>
          <li>• Custom domain on paid plans</li>
          <li>• Automatic updates</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="text-gray-700 mt-4"><strong>The reality:</strong> Export possible but not practical. Framer hosting is effectively required unless you want to rebuild the exported code.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Other AI Builders -->
      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Other AI Builders</h3>
        
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Wix, Squarespace, Webflow: Hosting included. All-in-one platforms. You're paying for hosting + builder + support bundled. No export means no hosting choice.</p>

        <p class="text-gray-700">Code exports: If you export code from any builder (messy as it might be), you can host it anywhere. See "Self-Hosted Sites" below.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Self-Hosted Options -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Hosting Exported Code (Self-Hosted)
    </h2>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">If you exported code from <AffiliateLink href="https://v0.dev">v0.dev</AffiliateLink>, Framer, or elsewhere, these are your best hosting options:</p>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <!-- Vercel -->
      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4"><AffiliateLink href="https://vercel.com">Vercel</AffiliateLink>: Best for React/Next.js</h3>
        
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Created by Next.js team. Best hosting for v0.dev exports. Seamless integration.</p>

        <p class="font-bold mb-2">Free tier:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-4">
          <li>• Unlimited projects</li>
          <li>• Automatic Git deployments</li>
          <li>• 100 GB bandwidth</li>
          <li>• Vercel subdomain</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="font-bold mb-2">Why choose Vercel:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• Built for Next.js (what v0.dev generates)</li>
          <li>• Best developer experience</li>
          <li>• Fastest deployment times</li>
          <li>• Preview deployments (test before production)</li>
        </ul>

        <a href="https://vercel.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="inline-block bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white font-black py-3 px-6 rounded-lg mt-4">
          Deploy to Vercel
        </a>
      </div>

      <!-- Netlify -->
      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Netlify: Best for Static Sites</h3>
        
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Excellent for static HTML/CSS/JS sites. Great for Framer exports or vanilla React.</p>

        <p class="font-bold mb-2">Free tier:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-4">
          <li>• Unlimited sites</li>
          <li>• 100 GB bandwidth</li>
          <li>• Automatic deployments</li>
          <li>• Netlify subdomain</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="font-bold mb-2">Why choose Netlify:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• Excellent for static sites</li>
          <li>• Build-time processing (if needed)</li>
          <li>• Forms handling (free tier includes)</li>
          <li>• Deploy previews</li>
        </ul>

        <a href="https://netlify.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="inline-block bg-green-600 hover:bg-green-700 text-white font-black py-3 px-6 rounded-lg mt-4">
          Deploy to Netlify
        </a>
      </div>

      <!-- GitHub Pages -->
      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">GitHub Pages: Free but Basic</h3>
        
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Completely free hosting for public repositories. Good for simple static sites.</p>

        <p class="font-bold mb-2">Free tier:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-4">
          <li>• 1 GB storage</li>
          <li>• 100 GB bandwidth per month</li>
          <li>• GitHub username.github.io domain</li>
          <li>• Custom domain supported</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="font-bold mb-2">Limitations:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• Static sites only (no server-side code)</li>
          <li>• Public repo required for free hosting</li>
          <li>• Slower deployments than Vercel/Netlify</li>
          <li>• Less polished developer experience</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="text-gray-700 mt-4"><strong>Best for:</strong> Personal projects, portfolios, simple sites where speed and features don't matter.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Traditional Hosting -->
      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Traditional Hosting (Not Recommended)</h3>
        
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Shared hosting (Bluehost, GoDaddy, etc.) is cheap but wrong choice for modern sites:</p>

        <p class="font-bold mb-2">Problems:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• Slower than modern platforms</li>
          <li>• Manual deployments (no Git integration)</li>
          <li>• Worse performance</li>
          <li>• Outdated server configurations</li>
          <li>• More maintenance required</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="text-gray-700 mt-4"><strong>Avoid unless:</strong> You have specific requirement that only traditional hosting can provide (rare for AI-built sites).</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Cost Comparison -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Hosting Cost Comparison
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-green-50 border-l-4 border-green-600 p-6">
        <p class="font-black mb-2"><AffiliateLink href="https://v0.dev">v0.dev</AffiliateLink> + <AffiliateLink href="https://vercel.com">Vercel</AffiliateLink>: $0-240/year</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Free tier: $0/year (with vercel.app subdomain). Pro: $20/month ($240/year) for custom domain. Best long-term value.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-purple-50 border-l-4 border-purple-600 p-6">
        <p class="font-black mb-2"><AffiliateLink href="https://durable.co">Durable</AffiliateLink>: $180-360/year</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Hosting included in subscription. Starter: $15/mo ($180/year). Business: $25/mo ($300/year). You're paying for platform, not just hosting.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-green-50 border-l-4 border-green-600 p-6">
        <p class="font-black mb-2"><AffiliateLink href="https://framer.com">Framer</AffiliateLink>: $60-360/year</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Hosting included. Mini: $5/mo ($60/year). Plus: $15/mo ($180/year). Pro: $30/mo ($360/year). Platform + hosting bundled.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-100 border-l-4 border-gray-600 p-6">
        <p class="font-black mb-2">Netlify: $0-192/year</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Free tier: $0/year. Pro: $19/mo ($228/year). Similar to Vercel pricing model. Choose based on preference, both are excellent.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6 mt-6">
        <p class="font-black mb-2">The winner:</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><AffiliateLink href="https://v0.dev">v0.dev</AffiliateLink> + <AffiliateLink href="https://vercel.com">Vercel</AffiliateLink> free tier = $0/year. Cheapest long-term option if you're technical. Durable/Framer cost more but include platform features and support.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How to Deploy -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      How to Deploy (Step by Step)
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <!-- Vercel Deployment -->
      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Deploy to <AffiliateLink href="https://vercel.com">Vercel</AffiliateLink> (from v0.dev):</h3>
        <ol class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>1. Create GitHub repository with your v0.dev code</li>
          <li>2. Go to vercel.com and sign up (login with GitHub recommended)</li>
          <li>3. Click "New Project"</li>
          <li>4. Import your GitHub repository</li>
          <li>5. Vercel detects framework (Next.js) automatically</li>
          <li>6. Click "Deploy"</li>
          <li>7. Site live in 30-60 seconds</li>
          <li>8. Push updates to Git → Vercel auto-deploys</li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <!-- Netlify Deployment -->
      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Deploy to Netlify:</h3>
        <ol class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>1. Create GitHub repository with your code</li>
          <li>2. Go to netlify.com and sign up</li>
          <li>3. Click "Add new site" → "Import an existing project"</li>
          <li>4. Connect to GitHub/GitLab/Bitbucket</li>
          <li>5. Select your repository</li>
          <li>6. Configure build settings (if needed)</li>
          <li>7. Click "Deploy site"</li>
          <li>8. Site live in 1-2 minutes</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Custom Domains -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Custom Domains: Do You Need to Pay?
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-bold mb-3">When you need custom domain:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• Business website (yourbrand.com looks professional)</li>
          <li>• Email at domain (you@yourbrand.com)</li>
          <li>• Branding and trust</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-bold mb-3">When subdomain is fine:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• Personal projects</li>
          <li>• Testing and MVP validation</li>
          <li>• Portfolios and side projects</li>
          <li>• Budget is $0</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-bold mb-3">Custom domain costs:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• Domain name: ~$10-15/year (Namecheap, Google Domains)</li>
          <li>• <AffiliateLink href="https://vercel.com">Vercel</AffiliateLink> Pro: $20/month (required for custom domain)</li>
          <li>• Netlify: Free tier supports custom domain</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Math:</strong> Vercel Pro ($240/year) + domain ($12/year) = $252/year for professional setup. Netlify free + domain ($12/year) = $12/year for same result. Netlify wins for custom domains on free tier.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Bottom Line -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <div class="bg-[#E07A5F]/10 border-2 border-[#E07A5F] rounded-xl p-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-black mb-6">The Bottom Line</h2>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">Hosting depends on which AI builder you used:</p>

      <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-700 mb-6">
        <li>• <strong><AffiliateLink href="https://v0.dev">v0.dev</AffiliateLink></strong> → Host on <AffiliateLink href="https://vercel.com">Vercel</AffiliateLink> (free tier is generous)</li>
        <li>• <strong><AffiliateLink href="https://durable.co">Durable</AffiliateLink>/<AffiliateLink href="https://framer.com">Framer</AffiliateLink></strong> → Hosting included (paid subscription)</li>
        <li>• <strong>Exported code</strong> → Vercel (best for Next.js), Netlify (best for static), GitHub Pages (free but basic)</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">Best overall value:</p>

      <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-700 mb-6">
        <li>• <strong>Free option:</strong> v0.dev + Vercel free tier = $0/year</li>
        <li>• <strong>Easiest option:</strong> Durable or Framer (hosting included, but expensive)</li>
        <li>• <strong>Custom domain:</strong> Netlify free tier + domain = $12/year total</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700">Don't overthink hosting. Start with free tiers. Upgrade when you hit limits. Vercel and Netlify make it easy to migrate later if needed.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Related -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-black mb-6 text-gray-900">
      Related AI Builder Guides
    </h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <a href="/v0-dev-review" class="block bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">v0.dev Full Review</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Free AI code generator</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/ai-website-building-guide" class="block bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">AI Website Building Guide</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Complete how-to guide</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
